description.narrative:
•	Two new health posts established; and drugs/equipments procured; all new arrivals medically and nutritionally screed and provided with necessary medical support;
•	Temporary shelters are provided to 13,400 families (13,400 plastic sheeting; and 67,000 bundles of sticks);
•	Primary education support provided for 20,100 students (30% of  population of 67,000 in first quarter of 2009);
•	Psychological counselling, child protection and GBV/SEA identification and support services in place;
•	Construction of two tented police posts;
•	Operational support provided to local and international NGOs.
